track_notes: Easy walking along the track through two gates.  Strike up hill on sheep tracks and indistinct paths, looking for easiest way through the small rocky outcrops.  Steep but easy. Note wall crossing at the top is via a stile.
Note wall crossings are at stiles, there is no need to climb walls. Indistinct paths and sheep tracks to follow.  Would be tricky in poor visibility.

A couple of gates to open which takes you onto a forest track. Drive for approximately 1/2 mile in the forestry and there is a parking area for a couple of cars where the route starts. A 4x4 would be a better option to take here, but the track is decent enough for a car if you miss the pot holes! The route is pretty steep and direct to the summit with a few boulders to climb over.
